🌶️🥵WHY WEDNESDAY: Season 1, Episode 2 with @elijahsxtreme!

Since 2014, this father and son duo has been rocking the hot sauce scene! Their business was created from a love of hot peppers and passion to create a more flavorful, thicker, hotter, hot sauce! 

These Charlotteans are now shipping their hot sauce to 170 countries! ✈️

FUN FACT: They have a hot sauce vending machine in Concord Mills Mall in front of Bass Pro ShopsHow cool is that?! 

📲Want to try their hot sauce for yourself? Order from their website: elijahsextreme.com!

➡️ABOUT THE VIDEO SERIES: 
We’re highlighting 16 different makers & doers right here in the Queen City! Each person tells us their story, how their business got started and WHY they do what they do! 

Every other Wednesday, we will release a new episode, highlighting another individual or business! You can only watch this on @exploreclt! We’re so excited for you to learn more about the people in this city! 🤩

“Pineapple-Mango Habanero Chicken with Cheese and Jalapeños is a mouthwatering dish with a perfect blend of sweet and spicy flavors.”

Ingredients: 
. 1 Chicken breast 
. Elijah’s Pineapple-mango habanero hot sauce 
. Salt and pepper to taste.
. shredded Mexican blend cheese 
. 1 jalapeño peppers, sliced (seeds removed for less heat)
.  fresh pineapple chunks

Instructions:
. Preheat your oven to 300°F.
. Cut the chicken into half then into strips.
. Season the chicken breasts with salt and black pepper on both sides.
. Brush the pineapple-mango habanero hot sauce,making sure they are well coated.
. Cover the baking dish with foil and bake in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through. Take out and cut into bite sized cubes, add some more sauce if desired. 
. Spread a generous amount of shredded  cheese on top of cooked chicken. 
. Arrange the jalapeño pepper slices and fresh pineapple chunks, on top of the cheese.
. bake for an additional 5-10 minutes or until the cheese is bubbly and slightly browned.
. Garnish with fresh cilantro or dried parsley,if desired.

Serve your Pineapple Mango Habanero Chicken with Cheese and Jalapeños hot and Enjoy!
